ity figures. FIFA says official counts reflect tickets scanned and fans inside the wider stadium footprint, not seats occupied at any moment — a defence critics say is undermined by pricing rows and withheld inventory.", "src": "ESPN / Yahoo Sports / SI / SVG Europe"}, {"cat": "tournament", "h": "All-time World Cup attendance record falls just six days in", "s": "Despite the empty-seat debate, the expanded 48-team Cup is pulling historic crowds: June 16 alone drew a record 281,223 fans across four matches, and more than 1.5 million had attended through June 17. Host openers for the USA, Mexico and Canada helped drive over 54 million TV viewers across the three nations.", "src": "ESPN / Yahoo Sports / FIFA / Goal"}, {"cat": "tournament", "h": "FIFA subpoenaed over ticket pricing as multiple states investigate", "s": "New York AG Letitia James and New Jersey AG Jennifer Davenport have subpoenaed FIFA over dynamic 'variable pricing' that lifted prices on 90+ of 104 matches by an average 34%, plus claims fans were reassigned to worse seats after new premium zones appeared. Texas AG Ken Paxton has opened a separate probe.", "src": "NY AG / ESPN / NPR / Gothamist"}, {"cat": "tournament", "h": "Visa rules and a travel ban keep many fans — and a player — from the U.S. Cup", "s": "A travel ban touching 39 countries, including participants Haiti, Iran, Ivory Coast and Senegal, has blocked most ordinary fans from those nations, while a since-suspended visa-bond program demanded deposits up to $15,000. On the pitch, Ghana's Thomas Partey lost his appeal against a Canadian visa refusal.", "src": "NPR / Al Jazeera / CFR"}, {"cat": "injury", "h": "Canada 'shaken' as Ismaël Koné suffers broken leg in Qatar rout", "s": "Midfielder Ismaël Koné was stretchered off with a fractured lower leg during Canada's 6-0 win over Qatar and has had successful surgery, but will miss the rest of the tournament. Coach Jesse Marsch said the squad was left shaken even as the co-hosts sit top of Group 